The '''British Society of Master Glass Painters''' (BSMGP), founded in 1921, is a [[United Kingdom|British]] trade association for the art and craft of [[stained glass]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.buildingconservation.com/directory/ad257.htm|title=British Society of Master Glass Painters - entry on the Building Conservation Website|website=Buildingconservation.com|accessdate=22 May 2017}}</ref> It promotes the trade, encourages high standards in the art and craft of glass painting and staining, and acts as a locus for the exchange of information and ideas within the craft, as well as helping to preserve the stained glass heritage of Britain.
BSMGP activities include: lectures, conferences, exhibitions, forums, guided walks and other events; an annual Journal, quarterly newsletter and other publications.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.craftscouncil.org.uk/craft-directory/organisations/view/?guid=8fa1288f-e6eb-4e&org_ref=3057&page=16 |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2010-10-15 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110727182332/http://www.craftscouncil.org.uk/craft-directory/organisations/view/?guid=8fa1288f-e6eb-4e&org_ref=3057&page=16 |archivedate=2011-07-27 |df= }} </ref> The Society also houses an extensive reference library and illustrated online design portfolios.
