{{short description|Papua New Guinean tribal art}}
'''Gope''' is a term for a spiritually charged carved board made to represent an Ancestral Hero in the [[Papuan Gulf]] of [[Papua New Guinea]].{{cn|date=November 2018}} Papuan Gulf people around [[Kikori]] and [[Baimuru Airport|Baimaru]] refer to these boards as Kwoi.{{cn|date=November 2018}} These sculptures<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.new-guinea-tribal-arts.com/|title=new guinea art|last=|first=|date=|website=new guinea tribal arts|language=en-US|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=2018-11-13}}</ref>{{failed verification|date=November 2018}} are often made from the sides of an old canoe.{{cn|date=November 2018}}

